article.headline: Wright St 72, Youngstown State 51
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Zakee Boyd was 4-of-6 from 3-point range and scored 22 points to lead Wright State to a 72-51 win over Youngstown State on Saturday. Wright State (5-5, 1-0 Horizon League) used a 19-6 first-half run to pull ahead 20-8 with 11:16 to play in the first half. The Raiders never trailed again and led Youngstown State (2-6, 0-1) 41-19 at halftime. The Raiders led by as many as 31 points in the second half, during which Boyd scored 12 of his points. Boyd, who shot 7-of-12 from the floor, scored eight straight points for the Raiders to make the score 66-36 with six minutes left in the game. Wright State shot 51 percent from the field while holding Youngstown State to 43 percent shooting. Drew Burleson and Zach Williams each added 12 points for the Raiders, while Dashaun Wood had 11 points and six assists. Quin Humphrey led the Penguins with 14 points, and Zach Silverman hit 3-of-4 3-pointers to add 12 points off the bench.
